description._content: Collection: Research Center Image Library Title: AC91-2008 Creator: NASA/Ames Research Center Description: This color image of the Earth was obtained by the Galileo spacecraft at about 6:10 am PST. The color composite used images taken through the red, green and violet filters. South America is near the center of the picture, and the white, sunlit continent of Antarctica is below. Picturesque weather fronts are visible in the South Atlantic, lower right. This is the first frame of the Galileo Earth spin movie, a 500-frame time-lapse motion picture showing a 25-hour period of Earth's rotation and atmospheric dynamics. Photographer: JPL ref # P-37330 Range: 1.3 million miles Date: 12/11/90 Source: www.archive.org/details/AILS_AC91-2008 Identifier: AILS_AC91-2008 SOURCE: nasaimages.org/luna/servlet/detail/NVA2~31~31~67490~128926 Visit www.nasaimages.org for the most comprehensive compilation of NASA stills, film and video, created in partnership with Internet Archive.
